Key Match Events: Dennis Man scored the first goal in the 40th minute with an assist from Răzvan Marin.
Dennis Man assisted Mihăilă, who hit the post in the 44th minute.
Răzvan Marin scored from a penalty in the 51st minute.
Kosovo made a triple substitution in the 66th minute.
Romania substituted Coman for Dennis Man in the 78th minute.
Denis Drăguș scored in the 82nd minute with an assist from Valentin Mihăilă.
Romania made further substitutions in the 83rd and 86th minutes.
Dragusin and Rrahmani received cards in the 90+5th minute.
Post-Match Reflections: This victory provides a strong start for Romania in the Nations League and offers a promising beginning for Mircea Lucescu’s new tenure as head coach.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match marked the debut of Mircea Lucescu as Romania’s national team coach after a 38-year hiatus.
The referee for the match was Aghayev A. from Azerbaijan.
The match was held at Stadiumi Fadil Vokrri in Pristina with an attendance of 12,872.
